            <div type="general">
               <p>Ouled Brahim (Saïda) is a community of around 19,000 in the Saïda province of the Department of Oran. The Ouled Brahim are not much different from other former Bedouins of Western Algeria: they are both farmers and shepherds. Their dialect is also very similar to other rural dialects of the region.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p>The only study on the dialect of the Ouled Brahim is
                  still <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:3XPRUXZE">W. Marçais (1908)</rs>, which was published in two parts. It includes chapters
                  on the phonology and morphology of the dialect, occasionally making comparisons with other Algerian dialects.</p>
            </div>

